args: Forest walks, are the best thing ever! ♪\nSo are snacks, I could eat 'em forever! ♪\nCleo's cookin' is somethin' to remember! ♪
Huh? I can hear a bunch of voices\nup ahead.
No one disturbs the peace of the forest\non MY watch! I'm going to complain!
Hey, they're all wearing the same stuff.\nWho ARE these people?
Cleo! Did you make any treats for us?
I've actually baked a berry pie.\nYou like those, don't you?
I LOVE 'em! Yaaay! Thanks, Cleo!\n...Wait, no! That's not why I'm here!
I saw a group of people all wearing the\nsame clothes. Do you know who they are?
Yeah! They were all bunched up in one\ncorner of the forest wearing the same\noutfit. Do you know anything about 'em?
I'm afraid I haven't the faintest idea\nwhat you're referring to.
I think the folks ya saw are students.

People who attend a school—a place
one goes to increase their knowledge.
There is just such a school in Rovetelle
on the edge of the forest.

Students often wear the same outfit,
which is known as a school uniform.
I imagine the people you saw came here
to gather herbs for one of their classes.
A uniform, huh? That's SUPER cool!
I dunno. Ya might still be a bit young.
I wanna wear a uniform right now!\nI wanna, I wanna, I WANNAAAAAA!
Your adultness is really shining through.\n...However, if you truly desire a uniform\nso badly, I could probably craft one.
However, it will take me a few days.
Very well. Let me take a look at the\nuniform of the schoolchildren you saw\nand go from there.
While I'm doing that, you should learn\nmore about what it's like to attend school\nfrom {player_name}.
Yay! I'm gonna learn everything\nthere is to know about schools!
...School? Well, it's a place where you go\nin order to study and make friends.
Sure. I mean, when you attend classes\nwith kids your own age, it's only natural.
Might you come here for a moment,\nMaribelle?
Mostly, but I need you in order to\nperform a proper fitting.
This is SOOO cute! It looks just like\nwhat all those students wore!
Well, it seems to fit all right, so I just\nneed to make a few finishing touches.
Then I can go to school!
...Oh? I didn't realize that was\npart of the plan here.
What? If you're wearing a uniform,\nyou get to go to school, right?
I wanna go make new friends!

I'm afraid it may not be quite that simple.
You will need the school to approve your
admission, as well as the permission of
your parent or guardian.
So if Granny says it's okay,\nI can go to school?
Uh, sure? Probably? So long as the\nschool's okay with it, I guess.
I'm gonna talk to Granny right now! Byeee!
She must really have taken to that\nuniform to be running off in it when\nit's not even finished.
We need to bring her back. It won't do to\nhave her running about in unfinished work.
Are you guys sure she's ready to be\nheadin' off to school on her own?
Perhaps it was a mistake to craft that\nuniform for her...
Don't worry about it, Cleo. This is\nsomething Maribelle decided on her own.
All we can do is watch and support her.\nI just hope she's all right.
